<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>The page you were looking for doesn't exist (404)</title>
  <style>
  body {
    color: darkgreen;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: arial, sans-serif;
  }
  div.dialog {
    width: 50em;
    margin: 1em auto 0 auto;
    border: 1px solid #CCC;
    border-right-color: #999;
    border-left-color: #999;
    border-bottom-color: #BBB;
    border-top: darkgreen solid 4px;
    border-top-left-radius: 9px;
    border-top-right-radius: 9px;
    background-color: white;
    padding: 7px 4em 0 4em;
  }
  div.dialog span {
    font-style: italic;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 100%;
    color: darkgreen;
    line-height: 1.5em;
  }
  body > p {
    width: 33em;
    margin: 0 auto 1em;
    padding: 1em 0;
    background-color: #F7F7F7;
    border: 1px solid #CCC;
    border-right-color: #999;
    border-bottom-color: #999;
    border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;
    border-top-color: #DADADA;
    color: #666;
    box-shadow:0 3px 8px rgba(50, 50, 50, 0.17);
  }
  .error-unicorn {
    margin-top: 15px;
  }
  .link {
    color: blue;
  }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- This file lives in public/404.html -->
  <%= image_tag('https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/564x/cc/19/00/cc190047a294500e964e94c963b09867.jpg', class: 'error-unicorn') %>
  <div class="dialog">
    <p>Oh no, what a <span>nightmare </span>!</p>
    <p>You may have mistyped the address or the page may have moved.</p>
    <p>Try clicking the back button, or just <%= link_to "go to the homepage.", root_path, class: "link" %></p>
  </div>
  <br>
  <p>If you are the application owner check the logs for more information.</p>
</body>
</html>
